              "free_text": [
                "    PULSED NEUTRON."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".TWO SAMPLES OF B10 WERE USED, BOTH OF 3.5 CM",
                " DIA. THE THICKNESSES WERE 2.737*E-2 ATOMS/BARN AND",
                " 6.086*E-2 ATOMS/BARN.",
                ".B10 93.0 +- 0.2 PC, SI 0.8 PC,",
                " B11 5.3 PC, C 0.7 PC,",
                " OTHERS 0.2 PC."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "    FLIGHT PATH = 50 M."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "    8 LI6 GLASS SCINTILLATORS NE 905, 4.5 CM",
                " DIA. AND 1.3 CM THICK.",
                " THE EIGHT SCINTILLATORS MOUNTED ON EITHER SIDE OF TWO",
                " ALUMINIUM PLATES. THESE PLATES WERE SET IN A VERTICAL",
                " PLANE, IN LINE WITH THE NEUTRON BEAM, WITH ONE PLATE",
                " FIXED ABOVE AND ONE BELOW THE NEUTRON BEAM TUBE,",
                " MEASUREMENTS WERE CARRIED OUT AT ANGLES OF 39, 65,",
                " 120 AND 144 DEG TO THE INCIDENT NEUTRON BEAM."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " ERRORS OF THE TOTAL SCATTERING X-SECT. IN MB.",
                " ------------------------------------------------------",
                " E0(KEV)                  1.      10.      70.",
                " ------------------------------------------------------",
                " STATISTICS              20.      15.      18.",
                " BKG NORMALISATION       22.      17.      14.",
                " DET. ANGLE              33.      12.       5.",
                " SIGMA TOTAL OF B10      26.      12.       8.",
                " MULTIPLE SCATTERING     63.      47.      37.",
                " TOTAL                   81.      55.      45.",
                " ------------------------------------------------------",
                ".BELOW 5 KEV THE OBSERVED DIFFERENTIAL SCATTERING CROSS",
                " SECTIONS AT 4 ANGLES START DEVIATING FROM ONE ANOTHER",
                " (AT MOST 9 PERC.). THIS IS MORE PROBABLY DUE TO",
                " INACCURACIES IN THE CORRECTION APPLIED TO THE DATA",
                " THAN TO THE EXISTENCE OF ANG.DEPENDENCE OF THE CROSS",
                " SECTION.",
                ".AVERAGED VALUE OF THE CROSS SECTION BETWEEN 0.92 TO",
                " 10.3 KEV IS 2.23 +- 0.06 B. AND USING THIS VALUE WITH",
                " A LEAST SQURE FIT OF THE TOTAL CROSS SECTION BY",
                " DIMENT, AERE-R-5224 (1967), THE CONSTANT DEVIATION",
                " DELTA-SIGMA OF THE (N,A) CROSS SECTION FROM 1/V LAW",
                " IS FOUND TO BE -0.28 +- 0.12 B."
              ]
            }
          ],
